1. Top and Bottom N Provider State By Discharge

Open Tableau Public. Select Text File data files and click open.





See data in Sheet Panel call (Data Source Panel), Schema Panel and preview panel. 


Go to WorkSheet and select Sheet 1.


Visualization Panel.  (Sheet1, Dashboard, Story data)


1.       Top and Bottom N Provider State by Discharge:

Create 2 parameters

Top N Provider State By Discharge and Bottom N Provider State By Discharge. right click on small icon on next to Dimensions Search and create parameter. 

Create parameter page open and select name of parameter, Data type and range button. then click ok. 

once creating parameter then right click on parameter and click shows parameter control and you will see right side the parameter that already created. 

Create 3 sets that combined with the parameter. right click on provider state in dimensions and create set. 

Set 1: Top N by Parameter: 

on Set page write name of set and choose By field. select Top and then select parameter which already created (Top N Provider state by discharge).  then click ok.

once created then drag and drop to the filter shelves.  select all and click ok. 



Set 2: Bottom N By parameter (Follow same as above)

on Set page write name of set and choose By field. select Bottom and then select parameter which already created (Bottom N Provider state by discharge).  then click ok.

once created then drag and drop to the filter shelves.  select all and click ok. 



Set 3: Top N & Bottom N Provider State:

once create 2 sets then create one more combined set. Hold Top N and Bottom N By Parameter and choose combined set. select choose all members in both sets. then click ok.




Drag and drop below selected Dimensions and Measures to the specific area.
